commit.message: * mule-caesar.el (mule-caesar-region): Use `ash' instead of `lsh'.

Update docstring syntax

"'" in docstring has become special character since emacs 25.
Non-special "'" should be escaped.  And, some '(' characters are
escaped with single "\" to avoid mis syntax highlighting.  But the
problem looks to be fixed already.  So I remove the workaround.

* filename.el (poly-funcall, filename-filters): Likewise.

* mcharset.el (default-mime-charset-detect-method-for-write):
Likewise.

* mule-caesar.el (mule-caesar-region): Likewise.

* path-util.el (add-path): Likewise.

* poe.el (character-to-event): Likewise.

* richtext.el (richtext-next-annotation): Likewise.

Fold docstring within 80 characters

* mcs-20.el (detect-mime-charset-from-coding-system)
(detect-mime-charset-string, detect-mime-charset-region): Likewise.

commit.message:
Fix fontset-pixel-size failure

* poem-e20.el (fontset-pixel-size): Don't check height, which no
longer exists since Emacs 23.

Revive poe.el's dependency on pym.el

* poe.el: Require pym.el.  pym.el is a part of poe.el.
Cf. https://github.com/wanderlust/apel/pull/10

Remove conditional definition of functions and variable.

Now all supported platforms have the same condition.

* emu.el (insert-binary-file-contents-literally): Remove
definition by defun-maybe.  The function is defined twice in the
same file and this part is second definition and never used.

* pces-e20.el: Don't require pym.el.
(find-coding-system): Define always.

* poe.el: Don't require pym.el.
(remassoc, remassq, remrassoc, remrassq)
(buffer-file-typesave-selected-frame, find-face)
(character-to-event, event-to-character, next-command-event)
(cancel-undo-boundary): Define always.

* poem.el: Don't require pym.el.
(char-int, int-char, char-or-char-int-p, char-octet): Define
always.

Remove codes for old platforms.

* pccl-20.el (ccl-accept-symbol-as-program): Remove check for
ccl-vector-execute-on-string.

* poe.el: Remove check for open-network-stream.

* poem.el (char-or-char-int-p): Remove check for char-valid-p.

Update package description file for MELPA.

* apel-pkg.el: Define supported Emacs version.
* product.el: Remove unneeded dependency on pym.el.
